lost_found_details.location_lost: New York Hilton Midtown, 6th Avenue, Manhattan, New York, NY, USA
lost_found_details.additional_information: I wonder if you could help me in the right direction. My mother has just been in New York this evening and left a bag in a yellow cab. The bag contained Medication, guess sliders, kindle, cozy cardigan charger and cable's for phone and kindle pandrops, purse with a few quid in it. The bag was purple rucksack. Nothing is of much importance but the kindle was the last gift given to her by my father before he passed away. 💔 it has sentimental value. The porters at Hilton Midtown, 1335, 6th Avenue hotel phoned a taxi and took her and three friends to the airport at 4pm on 10th of November. The transaction on her card shows : NYC TAXI 1246, LONG ISLAND C, USA. The cab driver had a pony tail and was missing a tooth, I know this is a long shot but any help would be appreciated. The cab fare was $114.05 and the last four digits of her card are 8919
